Implementation Plan for Preferred Install Locations

## Goals
1. Prefer user-local bin folders (~/.local/bin, ~/bin) when they exist and are in PATH
2. Fall back to ~/.sentry/bin only when necessary
3. Record installation metadata so upgrades work correctly

## Changes Made

### New Files
- src/lib/db/install-info.ts - DB operations for install metadata
- src/commands/cli/record-install.ts - CLI command to record install info
- test/lib/db/install-info.test.ts - Unit tests

### Modified Files
- src/commands/cli/index.ts - Added record-install route
- src/commands/cli/upgrade.ts - Added resolveMethod() helper
- src/lib/upgrade.ts - Updated detection and path resolution
- docs/public/install & install - Updated install script

## Install Priority Order
1. $SENTRY_INSTALL_DIR (if set and writable)
2. ~/.local/bin (if exists AND in $PATH)
3. ~/bin (if exists AND in $PATH)
4. ~/.sentry/bin (fallback, modifies PATH)

## Technical Details
- detectInstallationMethod() checks DB first, then legacy detection
- getCurlInstallPaths() uses stored path when available
- Install script calls 'sentry cli record-install --method curl' after download
